verses.text_plain: Ask ye of the Lord rain in the time of the latter rain; so the Lord shall make bright clouds, and give them showers of rain, to every one grass in the field.
verses.verse_html:
1Ask ye of the Lord rain in the time of the latter rain; so the Lord shall make bright clouds, and give them showers of rain, to every one grass in the field. ▼
▼ bright…: or, lightnings

verses.text_plain: For the idols have spoken vanity, and the diviners have seen a lie, and have told false dreams; they comfort in vain: therefore they went their way as a flock, they were troubled, because there was no shepherd.
verses.verse_html:
2For the idols have spoken vanity, and the diviners have seen a lie, and have told false dreams; they comfort in vain: therefore they went their way as a flock, they were troubled, because there was no shepherd. ▼
▼ idols: Heb. teraphims
 , ▼
▼ were…: or, answered that, etc

footnotes.body_html: ▼ were…: or, answered that, etc

verses.text_plain: Mine anger was kindled against the shepherds, and I punished the goats: for the Lord of hosts hath visited his flock the house of Judah, and hath made them as his goodly horse in the battle.
verses.verse_html:
3Mine anger was kindled against the shepherds, and I punished the goats: for the Lord of hosts hath visited his flock the house of Judah, and hath made them as his goodly horse in the battle. ▼
▼ punished: Heb. visited upon

footnotes.body_html: ▼ punished: Heb. visited upon

verses.text_plain: Out of him came forth the corner, out of him the nail, out of him the battle bow, out of him every oppressor together.
verses.verse_html: 4Out of him came forth the corner, out of him the nail, out of him the battle bow, out of him every oppressor together.

verses.text_plain: And they shall be as mighty men, which tread down their enemies in the mire of the streets in the battle: and they shall fight, because the Lord is with them, and the riders on horses shall be confounded.
verses.verse_html:
5And they shall be as mighty men, which tread down their enemies in the mire of the streets in the battle: and they shall fight, because the Lord is with them, and the riders on horses shall be confounded. ▼
▼ the riders…: or, they shall make the riders on horses ashamed

tokens.text: And they shall be as mighty

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the riders…: or, they shall make the riders on horses ashamed
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the riders…: or, they shall make the riders on horses ashamed

verses.text_plain: And I will strengthen the house of Judah, and I will save the house of Joseph, and I will bring them again to place them; for I have mercy upon them: and they shall be as though I had not cast them off: for I am the Lord their God, and will hear them.
verses.verse_html: 6And I will strengthen the house of Judah, and I will save the house of Joseph, and I will bring them again to place them; for I have mercy upon them: and they shall be as though I had not cast them off: for I am the Lord their God, and will hear them.

tokens.text: and I will bring them again to place
upon them: and they shall be as though
I had not cast them off

verses.text_plain: And they of Ephraim shall be like a mighty man, and their heart shall rejoice as through wine: yea, their children shall see it, and be glad; their heart shall rejoice in the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 7And they of Ephraim shall be like a mighty man, and their heart shall rejoice as through wine: yea, their children shall see it, and be glad; their heart shall rejoice in the Lord.

verses.text_plain: I will hiss for them, and gather them; for I have redeemed them: and they shall increase as they have increased.
verses.verse_html: 8I will hiss for them, and gather them; for I have redeemed them: and they shall increase as they have increased.

verses.text_plain: And I will sow them among the people: and they shall remember me in far countries; and they shall live with their children, and turn again.
verses.verse_html: 9And I will sow them among the people: and they shall remember me in far countries; and they shall live with their children, and turn again.

verses.text_plain: I will bring them again also out of the land of Egypt, and gather them out of Assyria; and I will bring them into the land of Gilead and Lebanon; and place shall not be found for them.
verses.verse_html: 10I will bring them again also out of the land of Egypt, and gather them out of Assyria; and I will bring them into the land of Gilead and Lebanon; and place shall not be found for them.

verses.text_plain: And he shall pass through the sea with affliction, and shall smite the waves in the sea, and all the deeps of the river shall dry up: and the pride of Assyria shall be brought down, and the sceptre of Egypt shall depart away.
verses.verse_html: 11And he shall pass through the sea with affliction, and shall smite the waves in the sea, and all the deeps of the river shall dry up: and the pride of Assyria shall be brought down, and the sceptre of Egypt shall depart away.

verses.text_plain: And I will strengthen them in the Lord; and they shall walk up and down in his name, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 12And I will strengthen them in the Lord; and they shall walk up and down in his name, saith the Lord.

tokens.text: and they shall walk up and down
